INSERT INTO contributions (idea_id, author_id, content, decision_log, status, view_count, submitted_at, created_at, updated_at) VALUES
(3, 4, E'# VaxPaw: Vaccine Schedule Automation for Independent Pet Shops\n\n## 1. Executive Summary\n\nVaxPaw is a lightweight SaaS platform that helps neighborhood pet shop owners track vaccination schedules for every pet they sell or service, automatically notifying owners when shots are due via SMS and email. By turning vaccine reminders into a repeat-visit driver, VaxPaw helps shops increase return visit rates by an estimated 25–35% without requiring a full-blown POS replacement. The platform targets independent pet shops handling 200–500 pets per month across grooming, boarding, and retail services.\n\n## 2. Market Analysis\n\n| Metric | Value | Source / Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| Independent pet shops (US) | ~12,000 | APPA 2024 National Pet Owners Survey |\n| Avg. pets registered per shop/month (target) | 200–500 | Owner interviews |\n| % of shops managing vaccines manually | ~71% | NAPHIA SMB survey 2023 |\n| Avg. rabies/DHPP vaccination cycle | 12 months (annual booster) | AVMA guidelines |\n| Pet owner no-show rate for booster shots | 38% without reminder | Banfield Pet Hospital study |\n| Avg. revenue per vet/grooming visit | $65–$120 | IBISWorld pet care report 2024 |\n| US pet care services market size | $30.2B | APPA 2024 |\n| TAM (reminder + CRM tools for pet businesses) | $420M | Grand View Research 2023 |\n\n## 3. Competitive Landscape\n\n| Competitor | Focus | Users | Strengths | Weaknesses |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| PetDesk | Vet appointment reminders | 10,000+ vet clinics | Strong vet market penetration | Vet-only, not designed for pet shops |\n| Shepherd Veterinary Software | Vet practice management | 5,000+ clinics | Full EHR + billing | Too complex and expensive for shops |\n| DaySmart Pet | Grooming + booking | 10,000+ groomers | Good grooming workflow | No vaccine tracking module |\n| 123Pet Software | Grooming + boarding | 8,000+ | Integrated POS | $89+/mo, no reminder automation |\n| Paper vaccine card | Manual | Most independent shops | Free | No automation, forgotten by owners |\n\n## 4. Target User Personas\n\n**Persona 1 — Kevin, 43, Independent Pet Shop Owner, Cincinnati OH**\nKevin sells puppies, kittens, fish, and birds. He keeps a paper binder of which puppies got their first DHPP shot and when the next one is due. He''s lost customers who came back for a booster and found out they were overdue — and embarrassed. He wants a simple digital record he can print or text to the owner.\n\n**Persona 2 — Stephanie, 37, Pet Boarding & Grooming Owner, Sacramento CA**\nStephanie requires proof of vaccination for all boarding guests. She currently asks owners to bring paper records each visit, and staff sometimes forget to check. She wants a system that maintains each pet''s vaccination history and flags overdue pets before they check in for boarding.\n\n**Persona 3 — Harold, 58, Multi-Service Pet Store Owner, Buffalo NY**\nHarold''s store offers grooming, boarding, and retail. He partners with a local vet who comes in on Tuesdays. He wants the vaccine reminder system to double as a scheduling tool — when a reminder fires, it suggests booking the Tuesday vet visit in one click. He''s not tech-savvy but his 26-year-old niece manages his social media and could handle setup.\n\n## 5. Core Features\n\n| Priority | Feature | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| P0 | Pet profile creation | Name, species, breed, DOB, owner contact info |\n| P0 | Vaccine record logging | Log each vaccine, date given, lot number, next due date |\n| P0 | Automated SMS + email reminder | Send reminder to owner 30, 14, 3 days before due date |\n| P0 | Shop dashboard | List of upcoming due vaccines this week/month |\n| P1 | Boarding check-in vaccine gate | Block boarding check-in if any required vaccine is overdue |\n| P1 | Owner self-service portal | Pet owner can view their pet''s vaccine history via link |\n| P1 | Vet visit scheduling link | Reminder includes one-click booking link for in-store vet days |\n| P2 | Multi-pet household management | One owner account, multiple pets |\n| P2 | Export to PDF (owner or shop records) | Printable vaccination certificate per pet |\n| P2 | Reminder analytics | Open rates, click rates, visit conversion per reminder campaign |\n\n## 6. Technical Architecture\n\n**Tech Stack:**\n- Backend: Python 3.12 + Django 5.0\n- Database: PostgreSQL 15\n- SMS: Twilio (reminder delivery + read receipts)\n- Email: Postmark (transactional)\n- Scheduling: Celery + Redis (reminder job queue)\n- Frontend: Django templates + Alpine.js (lightweight, no SPA needed)\n- Hosting: Fly.io (low ops overhead)\n- Auth: Django built-in + magic link for pet owner portal\n\n**Architecture Description:**\nVaccine due dates are stored in PostgreSQL with a computed next_due field. A Celery beat scheduler runs nightly at 7am and queries for pets with due dates in 30/14/3 days, enqueuing Twilio SMS and Postmark email jobs. The shop dashboard is a Django view refreshed on page load — no WebSocket needed given the workflow is not real-time. The pet owner portal uses a signed magic link (valid 7 days) to display the pet''s vaccination card without requiring owner account creation. Celery workers are deployed as a separate Fly.io process on the same private network.\n\n## 7. Business Model\n\n| Revenue Source | Model | Expected % of Revenue |\n|---|---|---|\n| Monthly SaaS subscription | $49/mo (up to 300 pets), $79/mo (301–600 pets) | 72% |\n| SMS reminder credits | $9/mo for 500 SMS (Twilio passthrough + margin) | 16% |\n| Printable certificate add-on | $4/mo for branded PDF certificates | 7% |\n| Setup fee | One-time $59 per shop | 5% |\n\n## 8. MVP Roadmap\n\n| Month | Milestone |\n|---|---|\n| M1 | Pet profiles + vaccine logging + shop dashboard + Twilio SMS reminders |\n| M2 | Email reminders (Postmark) + owner portal (magic link) + PDF export |\n| M3 | Boarding check-in vaccine gate + multi-pet households + reminder analytics |\n| M4 | Stripe billing + vet scheduling link integration + onboard 40 pilot shops |\n\n## 9. Success Metrics\n\n| KPI | M3 Target | M6 Target |\n|---|---|---|\n| Paying pet shops | 35 | 130 |\n| MRR | $1,900 | $7,200 |\n| Reminder delivery rate (SMS) | >97% | >98% |\n| Pet owner click-through on reminder | 28% | 35% |\n| Repeat visit lift (shops tracking) | +20% | +30% |\n| Shop NPS | 42 | 55 |\n\n## 10. Risks & Mitigation\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Twilio SMS cost increase | Low | Medium | Negotiate volume pricing at 50+ accounts; add email-only fallback tier |\n| Shop owners don''t log vaccines consistently | High | High | Frictionless logging (3 taps); offer CSV import from existing records |\n| Vet partnership not materializing | Medium | Medium | Make vet scheduling a simple custom link — no API integration required |\n| HIPAA-adjacent concerns for pet health data | Low | Medium | Pet health data is not covered by HIPAA; CCPA compliance for CA customers |\n| Competition from PetDesk expanding to shops | Medium | High | Move fast on boarding gate feature — defensible operational workflow |\n', '[{"step":"market_focus","decision":"Independent pet shops (not vet clinics)","reason":"Vet market saturated by PetDesk/Shepherd; pet shops are underserved and have simpler needs"},{"step":"tech_stack","decision":"Django + Celery (Python)","reason":"Django''s admin panel gives instant back-office without custom build; Celery handles reminder scheduling natively"},{"step":"reminder_approach","decision":"Twilio SMS + Postmark email (no app)","reason":"Pet owners don''t want another app; SMS open rate is 98%; zero download barrier"},{"step":"pricing","decision":"$49/$79 tiered by pet volume","reason":"Low enough for single-location shops to expense; high enough to cover Twilio COGS + margin"},{"step":"boarding_gate","decision":"P1 priority","reason":"Solving the boarding check-in pain creates operational dependency that dramatically reduces churn"}]', 'submitted', 33, NOW() - INTERVAL '38 days', NOW() - INTERVAL '39 days', NOW() - INTERVAL '38 days'),

(3, 9, E'# PetPulse: Loyalty-Driven Vaccine Reminder Platform for Pet Retailers\n\n## 1. Executive Summary\n\nPetPulse reframes the vaccine reminder tool as a customer loyalty engine. Each reminder sent to a pet owner is an opportunity to offer a discount on their next grooming or supply purchase, turning a routine healthcare nudge into a revenue-generating touchpoint. Shop owners get a CRM-lite view of every pet customer, their purchase history, and upcoming health milestones. PetPulse targets neighborhood pet shops handling 200–500 pets per month, differentiating from pure reminder tools by combining reminders with a points-based loyalty program.\n\n## 2. Market Analysis\n\n| Metric | Value | Source / Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| US pet industry annual spend | $147B | APPA 2024 |\n| % of pet owners visiting same shop 3+ yrs | 44% | APPA loyalty data |\n| Loyalty program lift on repeat purchase (retail) | +23% avg | Bond Brand Loyalty Report 2024 |\n| Avg. pet owner spend per visit | $78 | IBISWorld 2024 |\n| Pet shop owner top retention concern | Losing customers to PetSmart/Petco | Owner survey, n=80 |\n| Reminder open rate (SMS) | 98% | CTIA wireless data 2024 |\n| % of independent shops with loyalty program | ~18% | NAPHIA 2023 |\n| TAM (loyalty + reminder tools for pet retail) | $510M | Mordor Intelligence 2024 |\n\n## 3. Competitive Landscape\n\n| Competitor | Focus | Users | Strengths | Weaknesses |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| PetDesk | Vet appointment reminders | 10,000+ clinics | Deep vet integration | No loyalty, no retail focus |\n| Stamp Me | Digital loyalty stamps | 15,000+ SMBs | Easy loyalty setup | No pet/vaccine context |\n| Belly (acquired) | Loyalty for retail | Legacy | Was popular | Shut down 2022 |\n| DaySmart Pet | Grooming management | 10,000+ | POS + booking | No vaccine reminders, no loyalty |\n| Square Loyalty | Points program for Square users | 500K+ SMBs | Free tier, easy | No pet health context, generic |\n\n## 4. Target User Personas\n\n**Persona 1 — Tamara, 41, Pet Boutique Owner, Austin TX**\nTamara runs a premium pet boutique with grooming, organic food, and accessories. She loses customers to Petco every 6–12 months when they forget she exists between visits. She wants a system that keeps her top-of-mind: vaccine reminders keep her in the pet owner''s phone, and a points program gives them a reason to return for treats instead of going to the big box store.\n\n**Persona 2 — Ray, 49, Neighborhood Pet Supply & Grooming, Philadelphia PA**\nRay has 380 regular pets on file across grooming and boarding. He has no loyalty program. His biggest frustration: customers come in for a booster, spend $90 on supplies while they wait, and he has no way to track who his best customers are or reward them. He wants a simple points program he can run from his phone.\n\n**Persona 3 — Cynthia, 34, Cat Specialty Shop Owner, Portland OR**\nCynthia''s shop is 80% cats. She wants reminders to include cat-specific health content (FeLV, FIV testing reminders, not just rabies). She also wants to segment her reminder campaigns by species so she''s not sending dog vaccine reminders to cat-only households.\n\n## 5. Core Features\n\n| Priority | Feature | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| P0 | Pet + owner profile | Species, breed, vaccine history, owner contact, visit history |\n| P0 | Vaccine due date tracking + SMS/email reminders | Automated reminders at 30/14/3 days before due date |\n| P0 | Points loyalty program | Earn points per visit/purchase; redeem for discounts |\n| P0 | Shop dashboard | Upcoming vaccines, loyalty leaderboard, top customers |\n| P1 | Reminder + offer bundle | Each vaccine reminder includes a loyalty discount offer |\n| P1 | Species-based segmentation | Filter reminders and offers by dog/cat/bird/other |\n| P1 | Digital loyalty card (mobile web) | Owners view their points balance + redeem via phone |\n| P2 | Purchase history tracking | Log each visit''s services and spend for CRM insights |\n| P2 | Birthday + adoption anniversary reminders | Automated milestone messages with special offers |\n| P2 | Staff leaderboard | Track which staff member enrolls most pets in loyalty program |\n\n## 6. Technical Architecture\n\n**Tech Stack:**\n- Backend: Laravel 11 (PHP) + Laravel Horizon (queue management)\n- Database: MySQL 8.0 + Redis\n- SMS: Twilio\n- Email: Mailgun\n- Frontend: Livewire + Tailwind CSS (reactive UI without SPA complexity)\n- Loyalty Points Engine: Custom Laravel service with Redis atomic counters\n- Hosting: Laravel Forge + DigitalOcean Droplet\n- Auth: Laravel Sanctum (API tokens) + session auth (web)\n\n**Architecture Description:**\nThe loyalty points engine uses Redis INCR for atomic point accumulation, preventing race conditions during concurrent visit logging. A Laravel scheduler triggers daily reminder checks; jobs are queued via Horizon to Twilio and Mailgun workers with exponential backoff on failure. The digital loyalty card is a signed URL page (no login required for pet owners) that queries a read-optimized denormalized points_balance table. Species segmentation is handled via a tag system on pet profiles, allowing shops to build reminder audiences by any combination of species, breed, or vaccine type. Multi-tenant isolation via shop_id scoping throughout.\n\n## 7. Business Model\n\n| Revenue Source | Model | Expected % of Revenue |\n|---|---|---|\n| Monthly SaaS subscription | $59/mo (starter, 300 pets), $99/mo (pro, 600 pets + analytics) | 68% |\n| SMS credits | $12/mo for 600 SMS | 15% |\n| Loyalty program setup fee | One-time $79 for custom branding + points rules config | 8% |\n| Premium analytics | $19/mo add-on (customer LTV, species breakdown, campaign ROI) | 6% |\n| Referral commission | $50/referral when shop refers another shop | 3% |\n\n## 8. MVP Roadmap\n\n| Month | Milestone |\n|---|---|\n| M1 | Pet profiles + vaccine tracking + Twilio SMS reminders + basic shop dashboard |\n| M2 | Points loyalty engine + digital loyalty card (mobile web) + Mailgun email |\n| M3 | Reminder + offer bundle + species segmentation + birthday reminders |\n| M4 | Stripe billing + purchase history tracking + onboard 45 pilot shops |\n\n## 9. Success Metrics\n\n| KPI | M3 Target | M6 Target |\n|---|---|---|\n| Paying pet shops | 40 | 160 |\n| MRR | $2,600 | $11,400 |\n| Loyalty program enrollment rate (pets) | 55% | 70% |\n| Reminder-to-visit conversion | 22% | 30% |\n| Avg. points redemption rate | 35% | 45% |\n| Shop owner NPS | 44 | 58 |\n\n## 10. Risks & Mitigation\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Shops don''t track purchases (needed for points) | High | Medium | Make manual point awarding a tap; auto-award option for Twilio confirmation reply |\n| SMS opt-out rate from pet owners | Medium | Medium | Clear opt-in at enrollment; include opt-out in every message |\n| Loyalty program confusion for shop staff | Medium | Medium | Max 2 reward tiers; cheat-sheet laminate card for counter staff |\n| PHP/Laravel talent pool smaller than Node/Python | Low | Low | Laravel is mature and well-documented; Forge simplifies ops |\n| Big-box stores launching competing loyalty apps | Medium | High | Differentiate on local shop identity and personalization big-box can''t match |\n', '[{"step":"core_positioning","decision":"Loyalty-first, reminder-second","reason":"Pure reminder tools get replaced easily; loyalty program creates data lock-in and emotional stickiness"},{"step":"tech_stack","decision":"Laravel + Livewire","reason":"Laravel''s ecosystem (Horizon, Sanctum, Forge) covers all needs; Livewire avoids React complexity for a CRUD-heavy app"},{"step":"points_engine","decision":"Redis atomic counters","reason":"Prevents double-point race conditions during peak hours without complex distributed locking"},{"step":"loyalty_card","decision":"Signed URL (no app download)","reason":"Eliminates download friction for pet owners; signed URL is secure enough for loyalty balance display"},{"step":"segmentation","decision":"Tag-based species/breed segmentation","reason":"Flexible enough for any pet type without hard-coding species; cat-only shops are a real and sizable segment"},{"step":"gtm","decision":"Booth at regional pet industry trade shows (PETS+ Expo)","reason":"Independent shop owners cluster at trade events; in-person demo has 3x higher close rate than cold email for this demographic"}]', 'submitted', 41, NOW() - INTERVAL '30 days', NOW() - INTERVAL '31 days', NOW() - INTERVAL '30 days'),

(3, 12, E'# ShopShot: B2B Vaccine Reminder API for Pet Shop POS Integrations\n\n## 1. Executive Summary\n\nShopShot takes a fundamentally different approach: rather than building another standalone app for shop owners to adopt, it delivers vaccine reminder automation as an API and plugin layer that embeds directly into the POS and booking tools pet shops already use (Square, Vagaro, Booksy). Shop owners get the functionality without switching systems. ShopShot earns revenue from POS marketplace listing fees and a per-shop API subscription. This B2B2B model reduces CAC dramatically and targets the 200–500 pet/month independent shop segment via channel partners rather than direct sales.\n\n## 2. Market Analysis\n\n| Metric | Value | Source / Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| US independent pet shops using Square POS | ~4,800 | Square industry data 2024 |\n| US pet groomers using Vagaro | ~6,200 | Vagaro published partner data |\n| US pet shops using Booksy | ~2,100 | Booksy marketplace data |\n| Combined addressable via POS integrations | ~13,100 shops | Internal estimate |\n| POS app marketplace avg. install-to-trial rate | 12–18% | Shopify/Square partner benchmarks |\n| CAC via app marketplace vs direct sales | $35 vs $280 | Internal channel analysis |\n| Pet shop owner willingness to pay for reminder tool | 64% (if already in their POS) | Survey n=120 |\n| Integration-native tool retention rate | 78% at 12 months | SaaS integration study, ChartMogul 2023 |\n\n## 3. Competitive Landscape\n\n| Competitor | Focus | Users | Strengths | Weaknesses |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| PetDesk | Standalone vet/shop reminder app | 10,000+ | Direct relationship with vets | Standalone app = adoption friction |\n| Podium | SMB review + messaging | 100K+ | In Square App Marketplace | Not pet-specific, no vaccine logic |\n| VaxPaw (hypothetical direct competitor) | Standalone pet shop SaaS | N/A | Purpose-built | Requires shop to switch tools |\n| Square Appointments | Booking + reminders | 500K+ | Native to Square ecosystem | Generic reminders, no vaccine schema |\n| Vagaro | All-in-one grooming management | 70K+ | Strong grooming market share | No vaccine tracking module |\n\n## 4. Target User Personas\n\n**Persona 1 — Brian, 36, Pet Groomer turned Shop Owner, Denver CO**\nBrian runs all his bookings through Vagaro. He loves Vagaro and has no interest in switching to another system. He discovered a Vagaro app add-on that auto-sends birthday texts to pet owners and uses it religiously. He would immediately install a vaccine reminder add-on in Vagaro if it existed — it fits his existing workflow perfectly.\n\n**Persona 2 — Nadia, 29, Mobile Pet Groomer (van-based), Atlanta GA**\nNadia uses Square for payments and Square Appointments for booking. She has 280 regular dogs. She does not want a separate login for a reminder tool — she wants everything in Square. She would pay $19/mo for a Square app that auto-sends vaccine reminders from within her existing Square dashboard.\n\n**Persona 3 — George, 62, Traditional Pet Shop Owner, Cleveland OH**\nGeorge has used the same cash register software for 10 years. He recently switched to Clover POS because his accountant recommended it. He is not going to adopt a new SaaS product unless his Clover rep recommends it. An app in the Clover App Market, endorsed by Clover, is the only realistic path to reaching George.\n\n## 5. Core Features\n\n| Priority | Feature | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| P0 | Square App Marketplace plugin | Embeds vaccine tracking UI into Square Dashboard sidebar |\n| P0 | Vagaro add-on integration | Pulls customer + appointment data; injects reminder workflow |\n| P0 | Vaccine record schema + due date engine | Core logic: species-specific vaccine schedules, due date calculation |\n| P0 | Automated SMS/email reminders (Twilio/SendGrid) | Triggered by due date engine, branded per shop |\n| P1 | Clover App Market plugin | Clover POS integration with same feature set |\n| P1 | White-label branding per shop | Reminders send from shop''s name + phone number |\n| P1 | Reminder analytics dashboard (within POS) | Delivered, opened, clicked, converted to visit |\n| P2 | Booksy integration | Plugin for Booksy-using groomers |\n| P2 | Webhook API for custom POS systems | REST API for shops with proprietary or legacy POS |\n| P2 | Vet data sync | Import existing vaccination records from common vet EMR formats |\n\n## 6. Technical Architecture\n\n**Tech Stack:**\n- Backend: Node.js 20 + Fastify (API-first architecture)\n- Database: PostgreSQL 16 + Redis (job queuing)\n- POS SDKs: Square Connect SDK, Vagaro Webhook API, Clover REST SDK\n- SMS: Twilio\n- Email: SendGrid\n- Frontend: React 18 (embedded iframe plugin UI for Square/Clover dashboards)\n- Auth: OAuth 2.0 per POS platform (each platform handles auth flow)\n- Hosting: AWS Lambda + API Gateway (serverless, scales to zero between reminder batches)\n- Queue: AWS SQS (reminder delivery jobs)\n\n**Architecture Description:**\nEach POS integration uses the platform''s OAuth flow to obtain a shop access token, stored encrypted in PostgreSQL. Webhook handlers receive appointment/sale events from each POS and upsert pet visit records. The reminder engine runs as a scheduled Lambda (daily 7am UTC) that queries upcoming due dates and enqueues SQS messages for Twilio/SendGrid workers. Plugin UI is served as an embedded iframe using each platform''s app framework (Square App Framework, Clover App SDK). Because all customer data stays within the POS platform''s OAuth scope, ShopShot handles minimal PII directly — reducing privacy compliance surface area significantly.\n\n## 7. Business Model\n\n| Revenue Source | Model | Expected % of Revenue |\n|---|---|---|\n| Per-shop API subscription | $19/mo/shop (billed through POS marketplace) | 60% |\n| POS marketplace revenue share | POS takes 15–30%; net $13–$16/mo per shop | (included above, net basis) |\n| SMS/email volume overage | $0.015/SMS over 200/mo included | 22% |\n| Enterprise API tier | $299/mo for multi-location chains + webhook access | 12% |\n| POS partner integration bounty | One-time $2,500–$5,000 per new POS marketplace certified | 6% |\n\n## 8. MVP Roadmap\n\n| Month | Milestone |\n|---|---|\n| M1 | Square App Marketplace plugin MVP + vaccine schema + Twilio SMS reminders |\n| M2 | Square marketplace submission + review + Vagaro webhook integration |\n| M3 | Clover App Market plugin + SendGrid email + white-label branding |\n| M4 | Analytics dashboard + AWS Lambda migration + 100 shops via Square marketplace |\n\n## 9. Success Metrics\n\n| KPI | M3 Target | M6 Target |\n|---|---|---|\n| Shops installed (Square + Vagaro) | 80 | 350 |\n| MRR (net of marketplace cut) | $1,040 | $4,550 |\n| Square marketplace install-to-paid rate | 14% | 18% |\n| SMS delivery success rate | >97% | >98.5% |\n| 90-day retention rate | 72% | 80% |\n| CAC (blended) | <$40 | <$30 |\n\n## 10. Risks & Mitigation\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Square marketplace review rejection | Medium | High | Pre-review with Square partner team; use test sandbox extensively before submission |\n| POS platforms building native reminder features | Medium | High | Deeper vaccine schema + species logic is hard to replicate generically |\n| Low organic discovery in app marketplace | High | Medium | PPC within Square App Marketplace + SEO for "Square vaccine reminder" |\n| Revenue share reduces margin | High (certain) | Medium | Price at $19/mo knowing net is $13–16; build volume |\n| Vagaro API instability | Low | Medium | Degrade gracefully to manual CSV import if webhook breaks |\n', '[{"step":"go_to_market","decision":"B2B2B via POS marketplaces (not direct sales)","reason":"CAC via Square App Marketplace is $35 vs $280 direct; shop owners trust tools endorsed by their existing POS"},{"step":"tech_architecture","decision":"Serverless Lambda (AWS) for reminder engine","reason":"Reminder jobs are bursty (once daily); Lambda scales to zero between batches; no idle server cost"},{"step":"auth_model","decision":"OAuth per POS platform","reason":"Each POS handles user identity; ShopShot stores only access tokens; minimizes PII handling and compliance burden"},{"step":"plugin_ui","decision":"Embedded iframe in POS dashboard","reason":"Shops stay in their existing workflow; no tab switching; dramatically higher daily active usage"},{"step":"pricing","decision":"$19/mo to maximize marketplace install rate","reason":"Sub-$20 price point is impulse-buy territory; POS marketplace buyers rarely evaluate tools above $50/mo"},{"step":"mvp_platform","decision":"Square-first, then Vagaro, then Clover","reason":"Square has largest independent pet shop penetration; fastest marketplace certification; Vagaro grooming market second largest"}]', 'submitted', 57, NOW() - INTERVAL '26 days', NOW() - INTERVAL '27 days', NOW() - INTERVAL '26 days');

